You can see here, I am building an Eliza agent from scratch

```
import { AgentRuntime, type Character, type Plugin } from "@elizaos/core";
import { plugin } from "@elizaos/plugin-sql"
import { openaiPlugin } from "@elizaos/plugin-openai"
import fs from "fs";

// if .eliza directory does not exist, create it
if (!fs.existsSync(".eliza")) {
    fs.mkdirSync(".eliza");
}

const character: Character = {
    name: "Eliza",
    bio: "You are a helpful assistant",
};

const plugins: Plugin[] = [
    plugin,
    openaiPlugin,
];

const agent = new AgentRuntime({
    character, // need a character to start the agent
    plugins // bare minimum is db plugin and inference plugin
});

agent.initialize().then(() => {
    console.log("Agent initialized");


});
```

In order to get it to work I have to add
```
import fs from "fs";

// if .eliza directory does not exist, create it
if (!fs.existsSync(".eliza")) {
    fs.mkdirSync(".eliza");
}
```

But this should happen automatically
